replies.bodyText:
@sberyozkin I've updated the logic, if the algorithm doesn't match the predefined ones then we'll use it directly in PasswordFactory. This has 2 advantages

No need to build a custom exception, A predefined exception will be thrown by elytron if no such algorithm exists.
Users now can also use short form directly like "digest-md5".

@lower-case should algorithm property be enum:
enum Algorithm {
    DIGEST_MD5("digest-md5")
    //etc
}

Otherwise getAlgorithm does not do anything actually, you can pass algorithm as is anyway

